                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-637" type="given" value="WALTER EDMUND"></interp>WALTER EDMUND FITCH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker, and live at the corner of Dean-street, Oxford-street. These six balls were pledged with us by the prisoner on the 29th of August.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360919-name-638" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-638" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-638" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-638" type="given" value="HORATIO"></interp>HORATIO HUNT</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> These three are ours—one has a tinge on it—I know them well by that and the size—no one could have taken them but the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I bought the six of a Frenchman—when before the Magis<lb></lb>trate, he would not swear to them. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, I would not till I got the callipers to try them—they are two-inch balls.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The poor man was in distress, and going to leave the country—I gave him 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., for them—a few days after I wanted a little money and pawned them—I have moved in as high a circle as any man in England—I have served my King and country many years.</p>
